OL,3,CCould Loch Ness be turned into a giant
OL,4,Cwater battery?
OL,6,FAt least three private firms are
OL,7,Fplanning to do just that. Each has
OL,8,Fdifferent plans, but in essence they
OL,9,Fall want to move water between the
OL,10,Floch and reservoirs higher in the
OL,11,Fmountains - using the power as it
OL,12,Fflows back downhill to generate
OL,13,Felectricity.
OL,15,FThis would enable excess electricity
OL,16,Fproduced by wind, water and solar to
OL,17,Fbe stored for times when the sun isn't
OL,18,Fshining or the wind's not blowing.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G2/9
