OL,3,CCould Loch Ness be turned into a giant
OL,4,Cwater battery?
OL,6,FWhen there is excess electricity in
OL,7,Fthe grid - power is used to pump water
OL,8,Ffrom a lower reservoir to a connected
OL,9,Freservoir on higher ground.
OL,11,FWhen the electricity grid needs more
OL,12,Fenergy - for example on a dull calm
OL,13,Fday when solar and wind turbines
OL,14,Faren't producing more power - the
OL,15,Fwater is released down a giant pump.
OL,17,FThe gravitational force of the water
OL,18,Fflow from the high reservoir turns
OL,19,Fhuge turbines generating electricity.
