OL,3,CCould Loch Ness be turned into a giant
OL,4,Cwater battery?
OL,6,FAt full flow, enough water passes
OL,7,Fthrough the pipe to fill an Olympic
OL,8,Fsized swimming pool in 10 seconds.
OL,9,FIt's able to produce enough
OL,10,Felectricity to power one million homes
OL,11,Ffor 15 hours.
OL,13,FThat's nearly the population of
OL,14,FEdinburgh and Glasgow combined.
OL,16,FBuilding on this scale isn't cheap.
OL,17,FAccording to Roderick MacLeod,
OL,18,FDirector of Glenn Earrach Energy, his
OL,19,Fproposed project would cost #2 billion
OL,20,Fpounds and take eight years to build.
